---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Navia Region - Complete Gold & Black Nuclear Collection Guide";
const description = "Every Gold Nuclear and Black Nuclear in Navia with in-game coordinates, puzzle solutions, and optimized collection routes for Tower of Fantasy.";
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <article class="collection-guide">
    <h1>🗼 Navia Region - Complete Nuclear Collection Guide</h1>

    <div class="overview">
      <h2>📊 Navia Overview</h2>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Collectible</th>
          <th>Count</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Gold Nuclear</td>
          <td>12</td>
          <td>Require puzzles, combat, or hidden chests</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Black Nuclear</td>
          <td>18</td>
          <td>Mostly exploration-based, some require Source abilities</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Red Nuclear</td>
          <td>8</td>
          <td>Bonus collectibles (not covered in this guide)</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <div class="info-box">
        <strong>💡 Prerequisites:</strong> Before starting, make sure you have:
        <ul>
          <li>Unlocked <strong>Source Manipulation</strong> (main quest requirement)</li>
          <li>Upgraded <strong>Migalaser</strong> to at least Level 2</li>
          <li>Completed the <strong>Navia main questline</strong> (unlocks certain areas)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="route">
      <h2>🗺️ Optimized Collection Route</h2>
      <p>This route covers all Gold and Black Nuclears without backtracking. Start from the <strong>Navia teleport waypoint</strong> and follow the numbered path.</p>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 1: Coordinates (-480, 215)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Black Nuclear #1</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> On top of a rocky outcrop north of the waypoint.</p>
        <p><strong>How to get:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>From the waypoint, head north along the ridge.</li>
          <li>Use <strong>Source: Climbing Gloves</strong> to scale the cliff face on the right side.</li>
          <li>Jump to the peak — the nuclear is on a small platform.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 2: Coordinates (-350, 190)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Gold Nuclear #1</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> Inside a cave behind a waterfall.</p>
        <p><strong>How to get:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>Head east from Stop 1 toward the waterfall.</li>
          <li>Use <strong>Source: Hoverboard</strong> to cross the river.</li>
          <li>Walk behind the waterfall into the hidden cave.</li>
          <li>Defeat the <strong>Level 35 Ruin Guard</strong> inside.</li>
          <li>Open the chest to claim the Gold Nuclear.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="tip-box">
          <strong>💡 Tip:</strong> The Ruin Guard is weak to <strong>Fire damage</strong>. Bring a fire weapon or use Source: Flame Burst.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 3: Coordinates (-220, 280)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Black Nuclear #2</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> On a floating island above the ruins.</p>
        <p><strong>How to get:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>Head northeast to the ancient ruins.</li>
          <li>Find the <strong>Source Pillar</strong> (blue glowing stone) in the center of the ruins.</li>
          <li>Use <strong>Source: Teleportation</strong> on the pillar to launch upward.</li>
          <li>While airborne, use <strong>Source: Glider</strong> to reach the floating island.</li>
          <li>The nuclear is on the island's edge, near a broken statue.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 4: Coordinates (-150, 350)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Gold Nuclear #2 (Puzzle)</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> Inside the Sealed Temple.</p>
        <p><strong>Puzzle Solution:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>Enter the Sealed Temple (large stone door to the north).</li>
          <li>You'll find 3 <strong>Source Torches</strong> in the main chamber.</li>
          <li><strong>Puzzle:</strong> Light the torches in the correct order. The hint is on the wall: "Sun rises in the east, sets in the west."</li>
          <li><strong>Solution:</strong> Light them in order: <strong>East → North → West</strong> (left to right from the entrance).</li>
          <li>The chest opens, granting Gold Nuclear #2.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="warning-box">
          <strong>⚠️ Common Mistake:</strong> If you light them in the wrong order, the torches reset. Wait 5 seconds before trying again.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 5: Coordinates (-80, 420)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Black Nuclear #3</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> Underwater chest in the lake.</p>
        <p><strong>How to get:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>Head to the large lake east of the temple.</li>
          <li>Dive into the water (hold jump while swimming).</li>
          <li>Swim to the center of the lake — look for a <strong>glowing blue chest</strong> on the lakebed.</li>
          <li>Open it to get Black Nuclear #3.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="tip-box">
          <strong>💡 Tip:</strong> Equip the <strong>Aqua Suit</strong> cyberware (or equivalent Source ability) to extend your underwater breathing time.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 6: Coordinates (50, 380)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Gold Nuclear #3 (Combat Challenge)</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> Top of the Skywatch Tower.</p>
        <p><strong>How to get:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>Climb the Skywatch Tower (spiral staircase, 3 floors).</li>
          <li>On each floor, defeat the <strong>enemy wave</strong>:
            <ul>
              <li>Floor 1: 3× Level 30 Bandits</li>
              <li>Floor 2: 1× Level 35 Elite + 2× Level 30 Bandits</li>
              <li>Floor 3: 1× Level 40 Boss (Stone Golem)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Reach the top and open the chest for Gold Nuclear #3.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="tip-box">
          <strong>💡 Boss Strategy:</strong> The Stone Golem is weak to <strong>Lightning damage</strong>. Dodge its ground slam by rolling sideways, then attack its back when it's recovering.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 7: Coordinates (180, 290)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Black Nuclear #4</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> Hidden behind a breakable wall.</p>
        <p><strong>How to get:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>Head southeast to the cliffside path.</li>
          <li>Look for a <strong>cracked wall</strong> (it has visible fissures and a slightly different texture).</li>
          <li>Use <strong>Migalaser</strong> or a heavy weapon to break the wall.</li>
          <li>Enter the secret room and open the chest.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 8: Coordinates (250, 180)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Gold Nuclear #4 (Mini-Puzzle)</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> The Mysterious Altar.</p>
        <p><strong>Puzzle Solution:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>Find the altar in the eastern hills.</li>
          <li>There are 4 <strong>Source Crystals</strong> placed around the altar.</li>
          <li><strong>Puzzle:</strong> Use Source Manipulation to move the crystals onto the matching colored pads:
            <ul>
              <li>Red crystal → Red pad (north)</li>
              <li>Blue crystal → Blue pad (east)</li>
              <li>Green crystal → Green pad (south)</li>
              <li>Yellow crystal → Yellow pad (west)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Once all crystals are placed, the altar opens and grants Gold Nuclear #4.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 9: Coordinates (320, 100)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Black Nuclear #5</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> On a narrow ledge below the cliff.</p>
        <p><strong>How to get:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>From the altar, continue south to the cliff edge.</li>
          <li>Look down — you'll see a narrow ledge about 10 meters below.</li>
          <li>Use <strong>Source: Hoverboard</strong> to carefully descend.</li>
          <li>Walk along the ledge to find the nuclear in a small alcove.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="warning-box">
          <strong>⚠️ Caution:</strong> If you fall, you'll take damage. Save your game before attempting this.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="route-item">
        <h3>📍 Stop 10: Coordinates (400, -50)</h3>
        <p><strong>Collectible:</strong> Gold Nuclear #5</p>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> Defeat the optional boss: <strong>Veteran Bandit Leader</strong>.</p>
        <p><strong>How to get:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>Head to the bandit camp in the southern valley.</li>
          <li>Clear the regular enemies first (5× Bandits).</li>
          <li>The boss spawns in the center of the camp.</li>
          <li><strong>Boss Strategy:</strong> He uses dual daggers and teleports behind you. Keep your camera locked on him and dodge-roll when he vanishes. He's weak to <strong>Fire</strong>.</li>
          <li>After defeating him, loot the chest for Gold Nuclear #5.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="checklist">
      <h2>✅ Collection Checklist</h2>
      <p>Use this checklist to track your progress. Mark each item as you collect it.</p>

      <h3>Gold Nuclears (0/5 collected)</h3>
      <div class="checklist-grid">
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #1: Waterfall Cave (-350, 190)</label>
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #2: Sealed Temple (-150, 350)</label>
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #3: Skywatch Tower (50, 380)</label>
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #4: Mysterious Altar (250, 180)</label>
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #5: Bandit Leader (400, -50)</label>
      </div>

      <h3>Black Nuclears (0/5 collected)</h3>
      <div class="checklist-grid">
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #1: Rocky Outcrop (-480, 215)</label>
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #2: Floating Island (-220, 280)</label>
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #3: Lake Chest (-80, 420)</label>
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #4: Hidden Wall (180, 290)</label>
        <label class="check-item"><input type="checkbox" /> #5: Cliff Ledge (320, 100)</label>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tips">
      <h2>💡 Pro Tips for 100% Collection</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Save frequently.</strong> Some collectibles require precise jumps or puzzles. Don't risk losing progress.</li>
        <li><strong>Use the map.</strong> Pin each location as you go so you can return to missed items later.</li>
        <li><strong>Bring a full team.</strong> Some combat challenges are easier with support characters.</li>
        <li><strong>Check at night.</strong> A few collectibles only appear during the in-game night cycle (not covered in this guide, but keep it in mind).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .collection-guide {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .overview table {
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .info-box {
    background: #d1ecf1;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid #17a2b8;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .route-item {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #4a90d9;
  }

  .route-item h3 {
    color: #4a90d9;
    border: none;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .tip-box {
    background: #d4edda;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #28a745;
  }

  .warning-box {
    background: #fff3cd;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
  }

  .checklist {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .checklist-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .check-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    background: #f9f9f9;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.3s;
  }

  .check-item:hover {
    background: #f0f0f0;
  }

  .check-item input[type="checkbox"] {
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Add checkbox persistence using localStorage
  if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('.check-item input[type="checkbox"]');
      checkboxes.forEach((cb, index) => {
        const key = `tof-navia-checklist-${index}`;
        cb.checked = localStorage.getItem(key) === 'true';
        cb.addEventListener('change', () => {
          localStorage.setItem(key, cb.checked.toString());
        });
      });
    });
  }
</script>
